== Archiving ==
Is it easy to change the frequency of archiving for the various Reading Rooms. Wikibooks (or at least the Reading Rooms) is a lot less active than in the past and it's a pain returning after a break to have to plough through all of the various archives. Seems to be archiving everything after 21 days of no activity - would it be feasible to change this to 45 or 60 days? Also noticed that [[Wikibooks:Reading_room/Archives]] didn't have lists for 2013 so I've added them.--[[User:Xania|ЗAНИA]] [[Image:Flag_of_Estonia.svg|15px]][[User talk:Xania|<sup>talk</sup>]] 23:42, 17 March 2014 (UTC) : Each page should have a template call at the top to {{tl|User:MiszaBot/config}}. One of the parameters is&nbsp; {{nowrap|1=algo = old(21d)}}&nbsp; which can presumably be changed from 21 to 45 or 60 with the desired efect. I'd be okay with 60. --[[User:Pi zero|Pi zero]] ([[User talk:Pi zero|discuss]] • [[Special:Contributions/Pi zero|contribs]]) 01:24, 18 March 2014 (UTC) : Great so it's that simple. I'll give it a go some time. Thanks.--[[User:Xania|ЗAНИA]] [[Image:Flag_of_Estonia.svg|15px]][[User talk:Xania|<sup>talk</sup>]] 01:44, 18 March 2014 (UTC) : Done. Now 50 days. --[[User:Xania|ЗAНИA]] [[Image:Flag_of_Estonia.svg|15px]][[User talk:Xania|<sup>talk</sup>]] 18:07, 22 March 2014 (UTC)

