{{TRS-underconstruction|NEW=this page is the '''old original template basic usage''' sans updates. Many new modes were added last night as well as preliminary integration of Page to Page navigation logic. These options will be put up soon, time permitting&mdash;right after proof of concept and debugging of the page to page navigation in {{tl|TRS-hdrbox}} (subtemplate) has been validated.}}
=== Usage ===
;Purpose
:This template is used with {{Tl|FUN-bot}} to set off Trainz Beginner oriented and organized Wiki pages from intermediate, or advanced topics, and ''[[:category:Trainz reference pages|Trainz reference classed topics]]'' on the Wiki. It is a multipurpose template used on many pages of the Trainz Wikibook.
;Parameters and their effects

* The ''''''hold'''' parameter'' can be used to suppress the assertion of the {{tl|beginner links}} table and auto-TOCright.
:* Similarly, defining the named parameter ''''no''' to any value totally suppresses the beginner links, which merges the same controls across several header templates.
* It will not auto-categorize the page to the [[:category:Trainz fundamentals pages]], you must use {{Tl|FUN-bot}} to do that, which may be modified on this wiki to do page navigation.

* It can be given the <code><nowiki>{{{noTOC}}}</nowiki></code> parameter to suppress the automatic assertion of {{tl|TOCright}} moving the Table of Contents to the left margin in the default position. 

<pre>
</pre>
